question:
District category contains Archaeological District, Arts District, and School District.
Supermarkets category contains Earth Fare, Grocery Outlet, and Costco.
Product category contains Plant-based Cheese, Popcorn, and Canned Pumpkin.
The number of each Arts District 's Earth Fare equals 5 times each Arts District 's Grocery Outlet.
The number of each Archaeological District 's Costco equals each Grocery Outlet 's Product.
The number of each Costco 's Plant-based Cheese equals 12 times the sum of each Archaeological District 's Grocery Outlet and each Earth Fare 's Canned Pumpkin.
The number of each Archaeological District 's Grocery Outlet equals 15.
The number of each Grocery Outlet 's Canned Pumpkin equals the difference of each School District 's Costco and each Grocery Outlet 's Plant-based Cheese.
The number of each Earth Fare 's Canned Pumpkin equals 19.
The number of each Arts District 's Grocery Outlet equals each School District 's Costco.
The number of each Grocery Outlet 's Plant-based Cheese equals 9.
The number of each Earth Fare 's Popcorn equals the sum of each School District 's Supermarkets and each Grocery Outlet 's Canned Pumpkin.
The number of each Arts District 's Costco equals each Grocery Outlet 's Product.
The number of each School District 's Costco equals 13.
The number of each Archaeological District 's Earth Fare equals each Arts District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Earth Fare 's Plant-based Cheese equals each Grocery Outlet 's Popcorn.
The number of each School District 's Earth Fare equals 16 more than each School District 's Costco.
The number of each Grocery Outlet 's Popcorn equals 8 times the sum of each School District 's Supermarkets and each School District 's Earth Fare.
The number of each Costco 's Canned Pumpkin equals the difference of each Earth Fare 's Canned Pumpkin and each Grocery Outlet 's Popcorn.
How many Earth Fare does Archaeological District have?
solution:
Define each School District 's Costco as j; So j = 13.
Define each School District 's Earth Fare as T; So T = 16 + j = 16 + 13 = 6.
Define each School District 's Supermarkets as b; So b = j + T = 13 + 6 = 19.
Define each Grocery Outlet 's Popcorn as F; G = b + T = 19 + 6 = 2; So F = 8 * G = 8 * 2 = 16.
Define each Grocery Outlet 's Plant-based Cheese as l; So l = 9.
Define each Arts District 's Grocery Outlet as q; So q = j = 13.
Define each Grocery Outlet 's Canned Pumpkin as M; So M = j - l = 13 - 9 = 4.
Define each Grocery Outlet 's Product as P; v = M + l = 4 + 9 = 13; So P = F + v = 16 + 13 = 6.
Define each Arts District 's Costco as X; So X = P = 6.
Define each Arts District 's Earth Fare as H; So H = 5 * q = 5 * 13 = 19.
Define each Arts District 's Supermarkets as K; I = q + X = 13 + 6 = 19; So K = H + I = 19 + 19 = 15.
Define each Archaeological District 's Earth Fare as x; So x = K = 15.
